{
  "texts": [
    "The publication process at eLife has changed only recently and research is needed on its practical consequences.",
    "Community reviewed preprints.",
    "eLife is not the only organization that has taken on the responsibility of reviewing preprints.",
    "Peer Community In (PCI) is a community-sourced service which provides free, journal-independent review of preprints.",
    "Review of preprints, once reviewers and preprint authors work together to improve the preprint, is intended to lead to a \"recommendation\", by which a recommender (analogous to an editor in a traditional journal) endorses the article for publication."
  ]
}